Package: modelminer
Type: Package
Title: Automated Model Selection with Feature Engineering
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Jesse", "Brandt",
      email = "jesse.a.brandt@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Automated model selection that searches over polynomial terms and
    interaction terms to find the formula that best optimizes a user-supplied
    metric (default: AIC). Supports greedy forward selection, forward-backward
    stepwise search, backward elimination, phased greedy variants, and
    L1-regularised selection via lasso and lasso-path methods (requires
    'glmnet'). Works with any model function that accepts a formula and data
    argument, including lm, glm, and matrix-based models adapted via
    formula_wrap().
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
